review_blob: Damn good IPA, a real credit to its style with big hops and a nice bitterness.
Its a good cider, bright and fruity, goes down easy though nothing all that spectacular.
The flavor is anything but subtle...major hit of blueberries in both the nose and on the tongue, I could knock these back all day every day.
Clean tasting dark lager, a nice something to wash down a burger with but nothing too special.
Had a really strange sour taste to it, must be the rye, but I really didnt like this much at all.
A brilliant imperial stout, strong roasted malts with sweet undertone and this one WILL put you to bed.
Has the typical look and smell of a hefe, but a bit weak in the taste, a bit disappointing.
Transcendent, creamy coffee/chocolate taste with a nice kick of alcohol, this is the single best stout Ive ever had
beer_name: North Coast Old Rasputin Russian Imperial Stout

review_blob: Damn good, and the kicker is I had an old bottle, Ill have to retaste to see what its like when fresh
A nice example of the style, clean bright hops with just the right amount of bitterness
Not a bad beer, but does not justify its pricetag, youre paying for the name here
beer_name: Harpoon 100 Barrel Series #34 - Oak Aged Dunkel

review_blob: A very well balanced IPA, good blend of hop bitterness and malt sweetness, great beer to pair up with southwest food
Damn good IPA, and the label is just fantastic, another winner from Lagunitas big time.
beer_name: Lagunitas A Little Sumpin Sumpin Ale

review_blob: A really good IPA, has the strong bitter hoppiness with the light fruity backnote, a good example of the style.
Just a typical cheap pale lager, not as bad as some of the American biggies but still nothing special.
Magnificent, smoky with honey oak sweet taste, I would ascribe this to be maple-cured bacon on the list of Schlerkerla beers.
Another decent clean tasting German beer, cheap enough and easy to drink, and Im sure sales have gone up after its mentioning in Beerfest.
Lovely, much sweeter than normal hefeweizens but this was an absolute joy to drink on New Years.
Pale pour with floral honey sweet taste, certainly reminds me of other English blonds, and the label is amazing.
Incredibly dark beer with complex sweet taste with just a pinch of alcohol, I can see why theres been metal songs written about this stuff.
Nice clean beer, extremely easy going down, and a good value at $6.99/six at my local BD
Mild pale lager, easy to drink down, nice for when youre feeling like something a little different.
Pours a dark copper/red with a thin head, honey malt sweetness on the nose and taste, very strong caramel and toffee flavors, a heavier beer than the Tremens, but a winner nonetheless.
This is the best of the Lindemans lambics, immaculate black current taste with a hint of the sour lambic at the end.  I should really be eating a piece of cake with this.
Surprisingly easy to drink considering its alcohol content, mild sweet taste.
An excellent IPA, strong bitter hops all over this, yet easier to drink then other hop-heavy types of the genre.
Pours a beautiful copper/amber color, with a strong caramel scent, tastes of caramel, honey, with a bit of toastiness at the end, excellent.
A rather mild pale ale, pours out a typical gold color, flavor is there but much more subdued than other pale ales, not bad but could use some hops.
Deep dark gold color, lovely peachy hoppy scent and very strong citrus fruit and hop flavor with the requisite bitterness, excellent IPA
Deep gold color, sweet floral taste, rather typical Eurolager but not a bad beer to drink for the hell of it.
Dark pour with berry and herbal scent, taste is almost pure tannins though, so much so that it overwhelms everything else, only got a hint of berry at the end.
Gold honey-like appearance with floral scent and honey taste, good one to knock back
Typical pale lager pour and smell, has a mildly sweet taste with woody afternotes, not bad for a megalager
Bright gold pour with a medium white head, floral scent and clean sweet taste with fruity notes.  Really, really fine beer.
Oh yes, this is certainly an IPA...powerful hops on the nose and tounge.  Good representation of the style and the best Ive had from Brooklyn.
It tastes like a bad witbier with only a hint of ginger at the end...it looks nice but thats its only saving grace.  Really bad

beer_brewer_name: Magic Hat Brewing Company (North American Breweries)
review_blob: Magic Hat really needs to learn to stop labeling beers as something they arent...really an average brew here and not even resembling an Oktoberfest.
Dark gold color, hoppy scent and taste with that typical Otter beer aftertaste with some hoppy bitterness at the end...one of the better Otter beers
beer_name: Gilded Otter Rail Trail Pale Ale

review_blob: Delightfully strong hoppy scent, has the trademark hop and fruit taste of a well done IPA with a massive kick of bitterness, Stone produces another winner.
Its just a low alcohol version of Becks, and the bottle I had was skunked pretty bad, not really appealing.
A rather typical wheat ale, didnt really notice much of the gooseberry in the taste, had some fruit on the nose, a little disappointing.
Very rich caramel malt smell and taste with a syrupy mouth-feel, almost like drinking toffee with fizz, a very good ale indeed.
beer_name: Mendocino Eye of the Hawk Select Ale

review_blob: This is probably the most powerful fruit beer outside of a fruit lambic, straight blueberry smell and taste with a bit of wheat in the background, very refreshing and easy to knock back
beer_name: Sea Dog Wild Blueberry Wheat Ale

review_blob: Smells, and tastes like pomegrante.  Has a slight bit of hoppy bitterness at the end, a very drinkable brew, and pretty strong at 8%abv
Has a strong champagne scent and tastes like a dry wine with a hint of honey, didnt really notice the saffron all that much, a very different brew though quite enjoyable
beer_name: Dogfish Head Midas Touch Golden Elixir

review_blob: Has the look, smell, and taste of a saison, and a damn good one at that.  Bright gold color with fruity nose and taste with a hoppy finish, excellent indeed.
Straight out of the bottle with dinner, honey sweet smell and flavor with some toasty bitterness at the end, not bad at all.

Pours a nice deep amber/bronze, smells of dark fruits with a hint of caramel...tastes strongly of dried fruits, toffee, with a slight alcohol bite.  Does a very good job concealing the 9%abv, excellent beer.
Has the trademark smell of a good Imperial IPA, looks just like Coke on the pour.  Fantastic toasty chocolate/caramel taste with a hoppy finish, Stone gets it right again, the arrogant bastards!
beer_name: Stone Sublimely Self Righteous Black IPA
